We as members, contributors, and leaders pledge to make participation in our community a respectful and inclusive experience for everyone. 
We commit to creating a harassment-free environment regardless of age, body size, disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level of 
experience, nationality, personal appearance, race, religion, or sexual identity and orientation.

Our Standards
Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment:

Demonstrating empathy and kindness

Respecting differing opinions and experiences

Giving and gracefully accepting constructive feedback

Taking responsibility and apologizing for mistakes

Unacceptable behavior includes:

Use of sexualized language or imagery

Trolling, insulting, or derogatory comments

Public or private harassment

Publishing private information without consent

